edu.umaryland.igs.idea
Class ParameterSet

java.lang.Object
  edu.umaryland.igs.idea.ParameterSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PAMLParameterSet
public class ParameterSet
extends Object
implements Cloneable, Serializable

ParameterSet represents a grouping of parameters. Initially, the grouping was both a visual grouping and a grouping by parameter source (either PAML's .ctl file or the IDEA code). However, the display has been changed so that parameters are no longer grouped by source. Therefore, a ParameterSet can now represent either a visual grouping or a grouping by source, and a Parameter can now belong to more than one ParameterSet. Class ParameterSet is extended by class PAMLParameterSet.

public void addParameter(String name,
                         Object value,
                         String explanation)
This addParameter method creates a new parameter with the given name, value and one-line explanation and adds it to this parameter set. This is a convenience method for standard parameters with one-line explanations.

Parameters:
name - the name for the new parameter to add to this parameter set
value - the value for the new parameter to add to this parameter set
explanation - a one-line string explanation for the new parameter to add to this parameter set

                         Object value,

This addParameter method creates a new parameter with the given name, value and explanation and adds it to this parameter set. This is a convenience method for standard parameters with multi-line explanations.

addParameter

public void addParameter(Parameter p)
This addParameter method adds the given parameter to this parameter set. This method is useful for subclasses of Parameter. It is also useful for adding parameters already in at least one parameter set to another. For that reason, null parameters are ignored.

Parameters:
p - the parameter to add to this parameter set

getParameter

public Parameter getParameter(String name)
The getParameter method looks up the given name in this parameter set. If a parameter with that name is found, it is returned; otherwise, null is returned.

Parameters:
name - the name of the parameter to look up
Returns:
the parameter with the given name, or null if no such parameter is found in this parameter set

renameParameter

void renameParameter(String oldName,
                     String newName)
The renameParameter method is useful in loading configurations saved with old versions of IDEA. If the specified parameter is found, its name is changed, and the value in parameterList is also updated. If the parameter is not found, nothing happens.

Parameters:
oldName - the current name of the parameter to rename
newName - the desired new name

getParameterList

public LinkedList<Parameter> getParameterList()
The getParameterList method returns a linked list of the parameters in this parameter set. Note that this is *not* equivalent to the protected parameterList field because it is a list of Parameter objects, not just parameter names.

Returns:
a linked list of the parameters in this parameter set, represented as Parameter objects

entryArea

public JPanel entryArea(int displayColumns)
This convenience method passes the maximum name length for this parameter set to the two-arg version. It is to be used for parameter sets not tied to any other parameter set.

Parameters:

Returns:

entryArea

public JPanel entryArea(int displayColumns,
                        int maxNameLength)
The entryArea method returns a GUI component that lays out entry areas for each parameter in one or more vertical columns.

Parameters:
displayColumns - the number of display columns in which to lay out the entry areas
maxNameLength - the length of the longest parameter name in this set or any set tied to it
Returns:
a JPanel component to add to the GUI
